&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHO WE ARE 🌍&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Creating content that resonates is great — turning that attention into growth is even better. That&#39;s what Manychat does.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our AI-powered automations help creators and brands engage with audiences across Instagram, Messenger, WhatsApp, and TikTok — at the right moment, with the right message, minus the manual work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re 400+ people across three continents behind the leading platform for conversational growth, with AI skills shaping how we build, how we work, and how we grow.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHO WE&#39;RE LOOKING FOR 🌟&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for someone to bring AI to life across our entire Marketing org,&amp;nbsp; not in theory, but in the day-to-day work of every marketer on the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll sit embedded within Marketing, reporting to the Head of Marketing Operations and partnering closely with the CMO. Your mandate is broad and exciting: spot where AI and automation can unlock the most value, then build the systems, and the team capability, to capture it. You’ll decide what’s worth automating, design how it works, and turn a team of talented marketers into a team that builds and ships with AI by default.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a builder’s role with an enabler’s heart. One week you’re prototyping an agentic workflow that collapses a process from days to minutes; the next you’re sitting with a sub-team turning their biggest headache into something AI just handles. If you’ve been waiting for a role where “make us an AI-first marketing org” is the actual job description, this is it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;YOUR FUTURE TEAMMATES 👋&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Meet the Marketing team:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re the voice of Manychat. A voice that&#39;s loud, creative, opinionated, and weird in the best possible way. We combine passion, data, and storytelling to cut through the noise and fuel mad growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU&#39;LL DO 🚀&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead AI enablement across Marketing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Become the person the team turns to for “could AI do this?” and the one who makes the answer yes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coach and upskill marketers across every sub-team so they use AI and automation confidently in their daily work, raising the whole org’s AI literacy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run regular working sessions with sub-teams to surface high-value use cases, then prioritize the ones worth building&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion an experiment-first culture: test AI-driven approaches, measure what works, and scale the wins&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build the systems that make it real&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and ship AI-powered and automated workflows, building and maintaining automations, implementing MCPs, and working within GitHub repos and Claude.md configurations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Map customer data across our stack (Braze, our data warehouse, ad platforms) so information flows cleanly and stays consistent, including understanding Braze’s consumer event structure and the journeys it powers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set up, QA, and validate conversion events and tracking across Google, Meta, and TikTok&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build the connective tissue between our tools so the whole team moves faster&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Measure and prove the impact&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define success metrics tied to PLG outcomes: acquisition, free-to-paid conversion, and time-to-value&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Report efficiency gains and funnel improvements back to marketing leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build feedback loops that connect product usage data back into campaign targeting and segmentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&l

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHO WE ARE 🌍&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We help creators get more out of every conversation with Instagram-focused automations and support for other channels like Messenger, WhatsApp, and TikTok. The result? Better engagement, more sales, and real, sustainable growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With a diverse team of 400+ people spread across three continents, we’re building the leading Chat Marketing platform that is used — and loved — by more than 1.5 million customers worldwide.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT WE&#39;RE LOOKING FOR 🌟&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Manychat powers over a billion conversations a year. We need someone who cares deeply about every word in them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll write across campaigns, ads, social, and events. The briefs will vary. The bar won&#39;t. What we&#39;re really hiring is taste (oh and the craft to execute it at pace, across formats, without losing the thread of who we are, in harmonic collaboration with multiple other humans who care deeply about outcomes, not outputs.)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for someone with a genuine point of view on what good looks like. A portfolio that shows range and intention. The ability to channel a brand voice without becoming flat and obvious over time. The kind of person who rewrites a sentence at 11pm because it wasn&#39;t quite right, and nobody asked them to.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You concept (that is a verb now). You ask sharp questions before you pick up a pen (ask your grandma what a pen is). You take feedback without turning red in the ears, but can also defend a f***ing opinion. Nicely, pls..&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU&#39;LL DO 🚀&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write show-stopping event, campaign, and ad copy that makes people &lt;em&gt;feel&lt;/em&gt; something (and then click, if they wouldn’t mind).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build campaigns that spark conversation, screenshots, and Slack DMs that say “did you see this?”&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take creative swings that blur the line between art and strategy. BUT STAY ON BRIEF FOR GOD’S SAKE.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Channel the audience (creators on Social who mean business!) and our brand voice at the same time. Write like us, but for them. Does that make sense? It should.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re writing for the big leagues: Millions in ad spend, Webby-winning content, brand activations at the world’s biggest events. PSAs for every stall in the Austin bathrooms.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU&#39;LL BRING 💥&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A portfolio stacked with campaigns that were culturally resonant and moved the needle (we use needles here).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hopefully a combo of agency AND brand AND tech experience. Is that too much to ask for? Please at least check two boxes, but know that triple boxers have the edge.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The contact info of a few people who will swear by your work. We’re talking “I would not be alive today if not for their copywriting skills”.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Several years of experience doing all of this. My kid thinks ‘several’ means 6 to 9. Let’s go with that. In rare cases we’ll accept a mere handful years of experience.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oh and you’ll also have to bring yourself to an office in Austin. If Austin is far away, you are willing to make it much closer. We can help this happen with a cunning use of money.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT WE OFFER 🤗&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We care deeply about your growth, well-being, and comfort:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;📚 Annual professional development reimbursement for conference tickets, online courses, and other relevant resources to help you grow.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;💙Comprehensive medical, dental, and vision coverage for you and your dependents.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;🪴 Hybrid work and generous leave optio

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHO WE ARE 🌍&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Creating content that resonates is great — turning that attention into growth is even better. That&#39;s what Manychat does.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our AI-powered automations help creators and brands engage with audiences across Instagram, Messenger, WhatsApp, and TikTok — at the right moment, with the right message, minus the manual work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re 400+ people across three continents behind the leading platform for conversational growth, with AI skills shaping how we build, how we work, and how we grow.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHO WE&#39;RE LOOKING FOR 🌟&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Cyber Security Lead&lt;/strong&gt; — a technical security leader who can both run a team and stay hands-on. This role owns the full technical security operations function at Manychat: Application Security, Infrastructure Security, and Endpoint Security.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll manage a team of security engineers, define the operational roadmap across these three domains. Reporting to the &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.linkedin.com/in/kurzinmikhail/&quot;&gt;Head of Security&lt;/a&gt;, you&#39;ll be a key player in keeping our infrastructure and product protected and resilient.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU&#39;LL DO 🚀&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and grow a team of AppSec, Infra Sec, and Endpoint Security engineers (currently 3 engineers).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the end-to-end security operations function: detection, monitoring, incident response, and remediation across cloud, application, and endpoint layers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and execute operational roadmaps for Application Security, Infrastructure Security, and Endpoint/Office Security.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive adoption and administration of security tooling: EDR, SIEM, DAST/SAST, WAF, VPN, DNS security, and Okta.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee cloud security posture across AWS environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run and coordinate security incident investigations: root cause analysis, containment, remediation, and post-mortems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Infrastructure, IT Operations, and Engineering teams to implement and improve security controls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain security documentation: runbooks, configurations, playbooks, and operational procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support compliance requirements (SOC 2, ISO 27001) from the technical security side.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent cyber operations in cross-functional initiatives and contribute to strategic planning with the Head of Security.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;TO SHINE IN THIS ROLE 💥&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You&#39;ll need:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years in technical security roles across AppSec, Infra Sec, or Endpoint Security.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years in a lead or management role with direct reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with developer security tooling: SAST, SCA, secrets scanning, and DAST integration into CI/CD pipelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience operating and administering security tooling: EDR, SIEM,&amp;nbsp;DAST/SAST,&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;WAF, VPN,&amp;nbsp;and DNS security platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong AWS cloud security knowledge: IAM/SSO, Security Hub, GuardDuty, CloudTrail, and AWS Config.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid understanding of application security fundamentals: OWASP Top 10, SDLC security integration, and threat modelling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with endpoint security: macOS and Windows hardening, MDM (Jamf or Microsoft Intune).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to lead security incident response: coordinating teams, driving root cause analysis, and communicating findings clearly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills — able to translate security risk into business terms for non-technical

